File: Senzo Meyiwa was killed four years ago. BackpagePix/Sydney Mahlangu JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Bheki Cele declined to comment on a report regarding a gun allegedly linked to the murder of Orlando Pirates goalkeeper Senzo Meyiwa. News24 reported that police have identified a man -- who is in jail on charges of killing a Johannesburg taxi boss -- using the same gun. READ: Author lifts the lid on who might have killed Senzo Meyiwa "The gun found shouldn't make news, it should finalise and resolve the case," Cele said. "I heard that it is leaked, how do you expect the minister to answer on leaked issues? "I will leave them leaked. I will answer when I make statements and make an announcement."